user story
  customers have the right to get the most value out of programming by asking
  for small bits of functionality; programmers have the right to know what's needed
  a user story is the description of the behavior of the system, from POV of 
  system user

a story should encompass a week or two of programmer time
a programmer should have at least 1-2 stories per month

guru checks output
  check the output of a program just by reading it
  
a spike story
  just estimate or do a sketch mini problem of the whole big thing you're
  trying to tackle so you can get an estimate for the amt of time it will take
